##Literature Review
1. Deterding, S., Dixon, D., Khaled, R. and Nacke, L. (2011)
From game design elements to gamefulness: defining gamification. In: Proceedings of the 15th International Academic MindTrek Conference. ACM, pp.9–15.
Relevance: Provides a foundational definition of gamification and explains how elements like badges and levels contribute to user motivation—core to your engagement strategy.

2. Kietzmann, J.H., Hermkens, K., McCarthy, I.P. and Silvestre, B.S. (2011)
Social media? Get serious! Understanding the functional building blocks of social media. Business Horizons, 54(3), pp.241–251.
Relevance: Breaks down the key components of social media platforms (e.g., identity, presence, relationships), useful for designing user profiles and friend systems.

3. React Documentation (Meta, 2024)
Introducing React – A JavaScript library for building user interfaces. Available at: https://react.dev/
Relevance: Official source for using React to build modern, dynamic, and responsive UIs for your frontend.

4. Wilson, C. (2013)
User Interface Inspection Methods: A Guide for Engineers, Designers, and Managers. Morgan Kaufmann.
Relevance: Offers methods for evaluating UI/UX, supporting your testing and accessibility improvement process using tools like Lighthouse.

5. Fielding, R.T. (2000)
Architectural Styles and the Design of Network-based Software Architectures. Doctoral dissertation, University of California.
Relevance: Origin of REST architecture. Explains REST principles that guide the structure of your Django REST API integration.

6. Bakker, G. and Huinink, H. (2022)
Cross-platform development: Best practices for building applications on multiple platforms. Software Engineering Notes, 47(2), pp.45–51.
Relevance: Reviews techniques and frameworks for designing apps that work across web, mobile, and desktop—matches your cross-platform identity goal.

7. Zhao, D., Lu, Y. and Wang, B. (2020)
Building trust in social networking apps: Understanding users’ security and privacy concerns. Information & Management, 57(6), p.103319.
Relevance: Helps justify the importance of secure profile controls and trust features in your app, especially around friend permissions and visibility settings.

